<br>
If the Anti-TLC argument is:<br>
<br>
The TLC is broken and does not work as intended.  It prevents questing and thus warrents removel.<br>
<br>
Where are specific factual examples to support this claim.<br>
a) That the TLC operates outside its intended use.<br>
b) Quests are unsolvable because of the TLC.<br>
c) A &amp; B are sufficent and prolific enough to warrent remove of the TLC.<br>
<br>
My 'Pro-TLC' Argument is that there is not specific factual evidence to meet the above, and thus the 'Anti-TLC' arguement is based  on opinion and dislike of a core rule of the FV server, rather than factual evidence of damage to the intended game play on FV.<br>
