 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubjond.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bjond</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 126<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/31/01 10:20:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=935.topic&index=54>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Hmm.</span><hr size=1> I thought I demonstrated quite well that TLC makes quest solving literally impossible.  It does not make quest completion impossible if you have spoiler and if you have lots of resources (multiple comps/accs, plat, etc).  If TLC was in place on other servers, I would not have be able to solve the quests I did.  I don't mean complete -- I could have done that if someone else had solved them for me.  I mean it's not possible to do many quests from scratch with TLC and without spoilers.<br>
<br>
I did not and do not read VI board's.  I read these boards and pretty much everyone here was writing that TLC was intended to stop farmers.  That's ludicrous, since it doesn't stop farming.  If that's not the intent, then I have a problem with both the intent and the implementation.<br>
<br>
Lastly, I do not level race.  I've got 8 days played and am only 21.  If I level-raced, I'd be about 50 and I wouldn't have bothered mastering all languages.  I do not farm nor do I have a problem with those who do.  I do not have any problem with getting around the TLC myself.  I never said I did.  I've said it several times.  You keep coming back and saying I've got a problem getting around it.  I don't.  I've played 3 characters to post-50, one to 60.  Getting around TLC is no big deal for me even without reading spoilers because I did a lot of these quests back before there were spoilers.<br>
<br>
My problem is that TLC forces people to wait for other servers to solve quests and post spoilers.  It forces people to read these spoilers, weigh the reward and effort, and then work around the TLC instead of playing through the quest.  TLC hurts newbies, many of whom do not want to be spoiled.  It hurts people that don't scrounge for spoilers.  It hurts people that want to figure out quests for themselves.  It hurts those that don't have two accounts and two computers.  It hurts those that don't have a large stack of plat to pay lowbies.<br>
<br>
All of these things mean that TLC is good for people like me and really bad for most others.  I personally do not like an elitist atmosphere, even if it favors me.  That's what TLC fosters and it's the main reason I want it gone.  There are secondary reasons that are nearly important, too, though.  For one, not one single quest was designed with TLC in mind.  It's an afterthought that isn't really supported.  This makes questing doubly hard, since a quest bug here effects such a small number of people that it's not worth VI's time to fix it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uruss386.showPublicProfile?language=EN>russ386</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 34<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/31/01 11:07:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=935.topic&index=55>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hmm.</span><hr size=1> Denoi and Calare were able to complete quests without spoiler sites, true, but that really doesn't mean that those who are higher level than they are don't deserve to complete the quests.  TLC says to people who want to level, &quot;You're not welcome here&quot;.  &quot;In fact, we have a code in place that makes levels bad.&quot;  Then why not remove levels?  Make all mobs level 1.  VI could probably do it, with a little effort.  I just don't understand why the challenge of TLC is really necessary. It makes FV kind of elitist, in my opinion, like it's only for experts who ONLY care about quests.   I could write more, but it's New Year's Eve and I'm going to go party.  <br>
<br>
